summary: This is an email chain between FBI Special Agents in the New York Field Office discussing scheduling a call with an Assistant United States Attorney (AUSA) regarding Ghislaine Maxwell. The agents reference a piece of evidence recovered and note that one agent has not been involved with the case.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: The case being discussed for a call with an AUSA.

connections.description: FBI Special Agent M is being asked to discuss the Maxwell case with an AUSA, indicating involvement in the investigation.

events.title: Scheduling call about Maxwell evidence
events.description: FBI agents coordinate to schedule a call with an Assistant United States Attorney regarding evidence recovered in the Ghislaine Maxwell case.

keyFacts: FBI agents in New York were coordinating a call with a federal prosecutor about the Ghislaine Maxwell case in April 2021.
A piece of evidence had been recovered in the Maxwell investigation and was a topic for discussion.
One FBI agent noted they had 'not touched that case,' indicating a specific assignment or separation of duties within the investigation.
